<exercise id="fs-idp13838752">
<problem id="fs-idm89930880">
<para id="fs-idm10223552">What are the types of radiation emitted by the nuclei of radioactive elements?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm24069744">
<para id="fs-idm33283872">α (helium nuclei), β (electrons), β<sup>+</sup> (positrons), and η (neutrons) may be emitted from a radioactive element, all of which are particles; γ rays also may be emitted.</para>
