<exercise id="fs-idp102836704">
<problem id="fs-idp134914304">
<para id="fs-idp26162912">Why is electron capture accompanied by the emission of an X-ray?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idp165043872">
<para id="fs-idp123519008">The electron pulled into the nucleus was most likely found in the 1<emphasis effect="italics">s</emphasis> orbital. As an electron falls from a higher energy level to replace it, the difference in the energy of the replacement electron in its two energy levels is given off as an X-ray.</para>
</solution>
