<exercise id="fs-idm23721392">
<problem id="fs-idm88394912">
<para id="fs-idm29139968">Write a balanced equation for each of the following nuclear reactions:</para>
<para id="fs-idp133484688">(a) mercury-180 decays into platinum-176</para>
<para id="fs-idp136801104">(b) zirconium-90 and an electron are produced by the decay of an unstable nucleus</para>
<para id="fs-idp77337360">(c) thorium-232 decays and produces an alpha particle and a radium-228 nucleus, which decays into actinium-228 by beta decay</para>
<para id="fs-idm29267360">(d) neon-19 decays into fluorine-19</para>
</problem>
